                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1010">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.00/1684: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-31T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 31, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>543. In a speech which Velasco Ibarra has just made from the terrace of the
                    National Palace, he stated that he would name his Ministers within a few hours.
                    He stated that he is for democracy, will fight for democracy and will
                    collaborate with democracy; that his government will follow a “[apparent
                    omission] Colombia” policy. He promised freedom of speech and suffrage. He asked
                    the people not to spoil their triumph by any undignified actions as all America
                    is watching Ecuador and he promised that “justice will be done”.</p>
                <pb facs="1054" n="1040" xml:id="pg_1040"/>
                <p>Although I cannot say officially as yet, he is reported to have assumed power as
                    “Provisional President” and it is stated that he will call a Constituent
                    Assembly which will meet on August 10.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
